## Test Commands
```bash
# Run full test suite
pnpm test                    # or: npm test | make test | go test ./... | pytest

# Run a single test file
pnpm test src/auth/auth.test.ts

# Run with coverage
pnpm test --coverage

# Lint
pnpm lint

# Type check
pnpm typecheck
```

> Always run tests after every code change. Run lint before proposing a PR.

---

## Project Structure
```
src/
  api/          # HTTP route handlers
  services/     # Business logic layer
  repositories/ # Database access layer
  models/       # Domain types and schemas
  utils/        # Shared utilities
  config/       # Environment configuration
tests/
  unit/         # Unit tests (mirror src/ structure)
  integration/  # Integration tests (DB, external APIs)
  e2e/          # End-to-end tests
```

---

## Database
- ORM/query builder: <e.g. Prisma | TypeORM | Drizzle | SQLAlchemy | GORM>
- Never run migrations without explicit approval.
- Migration command: `pnpm db:migrate`
- Check migration status: `pnpm db:status`
- Never modify existing migrations — always add new ones.

---

## Environment
- Required env vars: `DATABASE_URL`, `REDIS_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `API_KEY`
- Use `.env.local` for local overrides (gitignored).
- Never commit `.env` files.

---

## PR / Commit Standards
- Commit format: `<type>(scope): description` (Conventional Commits)
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`
- PRs need: passing CI, 1 reviewer approval, no unresolved comments.
- Do not `git push` — propose changes for engineer review first.

---

## Secrets and Security
- All secrets via environment variables only.
- Use `process.env.SECRET` — never hardcode.
- Parameterize all SQL queries — zero string concatenation in queries.
- Never log request bodies that may contain credentials.

